data.meta_description: “I want to give visitors the impression that this isn’t just a museum, but a place for entertainment. My building should exude cheerfulness and bold design,” said James Stirling as he outlined his goals for the Neue Staatsgalerie in Stuttgart, whose architecture has enjoyed unusual popularity since the controversial competition decision.
